08/06/2006
ZAGREB, Croatia -- After wrapping up a two-day visit to Tirana, Danish Foreign Minister Per Stig Moeller arrived in Zagreb on Wednesday (7 June), where he met with counterpart Kolinda Grabar-Kitarovic. 
Their talks focused on EU integration, particularly on Croatia's progress and prospects in this respect. 
They also discussed new global challenges such as terrorism, with special attention to security in Southeast Europe. 
In addition, Moeller presented a special programme under which Denmark will provide funding for Croatia's public administration reform. 
Denmark is the current president of the UN Security Council. 
(HINA - 07/06/06)
